text: County Wicklow (Irish: Contae Chill Mhant√°in) is a county on the east coast of Ireland. It is directly south of Dublin. County Wicklow has an area of 2,024 square kilometres (781 sq mi). Wicklow is known as "The Garden of Ireland" because of its scenery. The county town is Wicklow. County Wicklow's largest municipality is Bray. Bray has a population of 30,951 and is not a suburb of Dublin. Other main towns include Greystones and Arklow. == Other websites == *Wicklow County Council *Map of Wicklow *Wicklow News *Pictures of County Wicklow, Irelandscape
